Challenge description:
Arghhhh! I forgot the code to unlock my phone and I'm too broke to engage Israelâ€™s Cellebrite Mobile Synchronization Ltd. to crack my phone. Can you help me to recover the code for some mad credz? http://web.spro.ink:3006

Prerequisite skills:
Extremely high dexterity OR the ability to script in Python

==========================================================================
From the webpage, we see a calculator like interface that asks for 3-Digit pin

We can open up the developer tools to record the network packets while trying a random key like "123".
We can see a POST request being captured and the form contains num="123"
[see challenge7.jpg file]

==========================================================================
In python 2.7, there is a module called "Requests" that can send POST request to a url.
We scripted a brute.py that send 000 to 999 and only inform us the PIN and the html response if flag is found.
[see brute.py file]

==========================================================================
milkyway@ctf101-shell:~$ ./brute.py 
The PIN is 042
